Quote: A feature of the threatened plants garden at Otari-Wilton's Bush is the shore spurge, Euphorbia glauca, which is also known as waiu-atua. This plant was thought to be extinct in the Wellington region till it was rediscovered on a  rock stack just off Kapiti Island in 1995.
